text.section:
A civil action for injunctive or other equitable relief for violation of an environmental covenant may be brought by:
A party to the environmental covenant;
The cabinet;
Any person to whom the environmental covenant expressly grants power to enforce;
A person whose interest in the real property or whose collateral or liability may be affected by the alleged violation of the environmental covenant; or
A municipality or other unit of local government in which the real property subject to the environmental covenant is located.
